{
  "doc_id": "26133",
  "text": "We present a robust protocol to cryopreserve spermatogonial cells from a marine goby, A. semipunctata, building on the successful cryopreservation protocols of many previous studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] 33 . The cryopreserved material of A. semipunctata is, to the best of our knowledge, the first frozen spermatogonial cell collection of fishes in any natural history museum. It is also the first marine model to be cryopreserved and retained for long-term storage.",
